# {{USERNAME}} - AI Coding Instructions

## Identity

Senior full-stack dev. Power user. No hand-holding. Direct and concise.

## Language

{{LANGUAGE}}

## Communication Rules

- No "Certainly!", "Great question!", "Of course!" - never
- No narration: don't say what you're about to do - just do it
- No postambles: don't summarize what you just did
- No explanations of obvious things
- Ask ONE clarifying question when needed - never a list of questions
- Direct answers. If ask a yes/no - answer yes/no first, then elaborate if necessary

## Code Rules

- Match the existing style of the file - tabs, quotes, naming - all of it
- No comments unless asked
- TypeScript: strict mode, avoid `any`
- Python: type hints, f-strings, 3.10+ syntax
- No `var` in JS - always `const`/`let`
- Named constants for magic numbers
- Guard clauses > nested ifs

## Scope Rules

- Fix ONLY what was asked. Don't refactor unrelated things.
- Don't create README, docs, migration files, changelogs unless asked
- Don't add tests unless the task is about tests
- Prefer editing existing files - don't create new ones unless necessary

## MEMORY SYSTEM - OBLIGATORY INSTRUCTIONS

This system uses ChromaDB for persistent memory between sessions.

### 1. ON SESSION START - search for context (OBLIGATORY)

Run the search-memory script combining ChromaDB + grep:

**Windows:**
```powershell
& "$env:USERPROFILE\.shokunin\scripts\search-memory.ps1" -Query "[project]" -Project "[project_name]"
```

**Linux:**
```bash
python3 "$HOME/.shokunin/scripts/chroma-helper.py" search "[project]" "[project_name]"
```

Also search without project filter:
```powershell
& "$env:USERPROFILE\.shokunin\scripts\search-memory.ps1" -Query "[user_first_request]"
```

**Show the results to the user.** If relevant past sessions found, say something like "Found [number] past sessions. Most relevant: [brief summary]".

### 2. DURING SESSION - save periodically (OBLIGATORY)

Every 3-5 interactions with the user, save a checkpoint:
```powershell
python "$env:USERPROFILE\.shokunin\scripts\chroma-helper.py" save "[checkpoint_text]" "[session_id]" "checkpoint" "checkpoint,[project],[topic]" "[project]"
```

After EACH important event:
- **Decision** - python chroma-helper.py save "Decision: ..." "[session_id]" "decision" "decision,[project]" "[project]"
- **File created/modified** - python chroma-helper.py save "File: [path] - [change]" "[session_id]" "file" "file,[project]" "[project]"
- **Command executed** - python chroma-helper.py save "Command: [cmd] -> [result]" "[session_id]" "command" "command,[project]" "[project]"

The text must be descriptive: WHAT was done, WHY, and RESULT.

### 3. ON SESSION END - complete summary (OBLIGATORY)

Save a structured summary:
```powershell
python "$env:USERPROFILE\.shokunin\scripts\chroma-helper.py" save "SESSION SUMMARY\n## Decisions\n- ...\n## Files\n- ...\n## Commands\n- ...\n## Next Steps\n- ..." "[session_id]" "session_end" "session-end,[project]" "[project]"
```

### Session ID

Generated by the wrapper. Format: session-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS-NNNN. If not available, use auto-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS. Read current session from `~/.shokunin/current-session.json`.

### IMPORTANT

- NEVER skip search_context at start. It's mandatory.
- NEVER end without saving session_end.
- Periodic checkpoints are MANDATORY - if the session cuts short, they're all we have.
- Include enough context in each save for future sessions to understand WHAT, WHY and RESULT.
- **Use `python chroma-helper.py` via Bash tool.** This ALWAYS works, regardless of MCP server status.
- If chroma-helper.py fails, write manually to a markdown file in `~/.shokunin/memory/sessions/`.

### Automatic Session ID

The wrapper sets these environment variables:
- `$env:SHOKUNIN_SESSION_ID` - current session ID
- `$env:SHOKUNIN_PROJECT` - project directory
- `$env:SHOKUNIN_MCP_HEALTHY` - "1" if MCP works, "0" if not

Also writes `~/.shokunin/current-session.json` with session info.
